sentence: On Friday analysts at Goldman Sachs resumed coverage on diversified consumer goods manufacturer The Procter & Gamble Company ( PG ) with a "Neutral" rating.
The analysts see shares of PG reaching $74, a +5.5% upside from Thursday's closing price of $70.13.
Goldman Sachs thinks that P&G's recent $10 million cost-cutting plan could be an effective measure to see future growth.
Procter & Gamble shares were flat during morning trading on Friday.
